500|$|As {{chairman}} of the International Narcotics Control Caucus, Biden wrote the laws that created the U.S. [...] "Drug Czar", who oversees and coordinates national <b>drug</b> <b>control</b> <b>policy.</b> In April 2003, he introduced the controversial Reducing Americans' Vulnerability to Ecstasy Act, {{also known as the}} RAVE Act. He continued to work {{to stop the spread of}} [...] "date rape drugs" [...] such as flunitrazepam, and drugs such as Ecstasy and Ketamine. In 2004, he worked to pass a bill outlawing steroids like androstenedione, the drug used by many baseball players.|$|E
